  "prompt": "Can I use WhatsApp with a different number than the cell phone I have it installed in without changing sims just adding the other number?",
  "response": "WhatsApp doesn't support using multiple phone numbers on the same device without changing SIM cards. However, you have a few alternative options:\n\n1. WhatsApp Business: You can have a separate WhatsApp Business account alongside your regular WhatsApp account.\n\n2. WhatsApp Multi-Device: This feature allows you to use WhatsApp on multiple devices, but it still requires your primary phone number.\n\n3. Third-party apps: Some apps like Parallel Space or Dual Space can help you clone WhatsApp, but these aren't officially supported and may have security risks.\n\n4. Temporary solutions:\n- Use WhatsApp Web/Desktop\n- Use a virtual phone number service\n- Use WhatsApp linked devices feature\n\nThe most straightforward way to use a different number is to:\n- Backup your current WhatsApp data\n- Uninstall WhatsApp\n- Reinstall and verify with the new number\n- Restore your backup\n\nIf you frequently need to switch between numbers, these methods might help, but they're not as convenient as having multiple numbers simultaneously on one app.",
